        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 11:54PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1153 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Rotan, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rotan and Hobbs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for west central
Texas.</instruction>
